AB  - This study examines two important issues underlying realized volatility and correlation estimators. First, an empirical inquiry is conducted to assess whether Bax and Eurodollar futures tick-by-tick data can be characterized as marked-point processes. Second, ARMA, neural network, GARCH-BEKK, and naive volatility and correlation forecasts are compared in an out-of-sample context when a trader prices an interest rate spread option based on those forecasts and simultaneously delta-hedges her position. Other loss functions are also considered. Competing volatility forecasts are also compared to implied volatilities.
ER  - 

